  "title": "Investment Banking Associate SEA",
  "description": "<p><strong>About The Role</strong></p><p>As an Associate, you will be expected to focus on advancing client relationships, creating and analysing financial models, creating client presentations and transaction support.  </p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>· Gather company data and operating information on\ncompanies </p><p>· Evaluate market data and perform financial\nmodelling to analyse trends and help value companies</p><p>· Prepare and present M&A opportunity and\nbusiness strategy materials for clients</p><p>· Be actively involved in execution of\nhigh-profile and prominent transactions in the Asia Pacific region  </p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree from a leading university in Finance or related disciplines with excellent academic results </li><li>Previous investment banking experience in deal/ transaction support preferred, M&A experience from Big 4 Accounting Firms (or similar) will be considered. </li><li>Technically sound with practical financial modelling skills </li><li>An analytical mindset with solid knowledge of accounting, financial and operational concepts </li><li>Commitment to delivery of highest quality work product </li><li>Ability to effectively prioritize and handle multiple tasks under tight deadlines </li><li>Excellent team player with demonstrated good management skills </li><li>Demonstrate best in class professional integrity </li><li>Proactive, positive, self-motivated and goal-oriented </li></ul>",
